Ignite your FIRE to become the best version of yourself ! I’ve found my fire, have you? 🔥

I’m proud to announce myself as the Global Brand Ambassador for FIRE-BOLTT, India’s No.1 Smartwatch Brand @fireboltt_

I love that Fireboltt is helping India become fitter, look smarter and work faster.

Here’s your chance to #FindYourFire and become a part of our clan by participating in the massive 1000 SMARTWATCH GIVEAWAY ‼️

Just #FollowFireboltt and participate in the contest running on their page and you can win a free smartwatch 🔥

You can also AVAIL 10% OFF using my code “VIRAT01” on www.fireboltt.com

node.text:
I couldn't explain the mutual trust, respect and understanding we share better than these two videos I'm posting here today.
The first one explains perfectly well who he is , selfless in the most intense moments. 
The second one is about the kind of trust & chemistry we had over the years while batting together. In this moment I was only focused on his call & I knew we both would be able to make those 2 runs because of the trust we shared in one another. He called & I put my head down and ran ! 
Mutual respect and understanding isn't a thing of chance, it develops naturally when two individuals are aligned & have the same vision and for us, that vision was always to make India win ! Thank you for all these memories skip. 🇮🇳💙@mahi7781

video credit- @starsportsindia @icc

node.text:
He taught me to never rely on shortcuts or influence — because if you truly have it in you, hard work will show it.
And if you don’t have the will to work for it, then maybe you don’t deserve it yet.

When I was offered an easier path once, he refused it for me.
With calm conviction, he said, “If you’re good enough, you’ll find your way. And if not, it’s better to know that early.”

That one moment shaped how I live, work, and show up in the world.
Happy Father’s Day to all the fathers whose quiet strength becomes our lifelong compass. ❤️

node.text: I’ve seen it for 18 years and she’s seen it for 11. Suffered the same moments since 2014 and celebrated every close win and the madness of our supporters at the Chinnaswamy. We’re both equally relieved and since shes a bangalore girl too this is far more special for her. Together all the way through ❤️❤️❤️ @anushkasharma

node.text: This team made the dream possible , a season I’ll never ever forget. We’ve thoroughly enjoyed the ride over the last 2.5 months. This one is for the fans of rcb who never ever left our side in the worst of times. This one is for all the years of heartbreaks and disappointment. This is for every inch of effort left on the field playing for this team. As far as the ipl trophy is concerned- you’ve made me wait 18 years to be able to lift you and celebrate my friend, but it’s been absolutely worth the wait. ❤️ 🏆@royalchallengers.bengaluru

node.text:
You all know how much I love my beard - there’s no chance I’d trust it with just any trimmer. That’s why I go with the Philips All In One Trimmer! With its unique Beardsense Technology, it scans my beard 125 times per second and adapts to it. That’s not just precision—it’s like having 125 barbers at work. After all, Philips aur baaki trimmers mein 19 – 20 ka nahi, 125 ka farak hai!

#PhilipsAllInOne #Trimmer #Philips #125KaFarak

node.text:
They’ll talk about the records and the milestones — but I’ll remember the tears you never showed, the battles no one saw, and the unwavering love you gave this format of the game. I know how much all this took from you. After every Test series, you came back a little wiser, a little humbler — and watching you evolve through it all has been a privilege.

Somehow, I always imagined you’d retire international cricket in whites — But you’ve always followed your heart, and so I just want to say my love, you’ve earned every bit of this goodbye ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Virat Kohli on May 11, 2025. 1 व्यक्ति, playing cricket और वह टेक्स्ट जिसमें 'VIFAT' लिखा है की फ़ोटो हो सकती है.

node.text:
It’s been 14 years since I first wore the baggy blue in Test cricket. Honestly, I never imagined the journey this format would take me on. It’s tested me, shaped me, and taught me lessons I’ll carry for life.

There’s something deeply personal about playing in whites. The quiet grind, the long days, the small moments that no one sees but that stay with you forever.

As I step away from this format, it’s not easy — but it feels right. I’ve given it everything I had, and it’s given me back so much more than I could’ve hoped for.

I’m walking away with a heart full of gratitude — for the game, for the people I shared the field with, and for every single person who made me feel seen along the way.

I’ll always look back at my Test career with a smile.

#269, signing off.
🇮🇳❤️
